text.section:
The Committee shall:
Adopt a seal which shall be judicially noticed;
Offer assistance to the supervisors of soil conservation districts;
Keep the supervisors of each district informed of the activities and experience of the other districts and facilitate cooperation and interchange of advice and experience between the districts;
Coordinate the programs of the several soil conservation districts by advising and consulting with the districts;
Secure the cooperation and assistance of the United States, its agencies, and State agencies in the work of the districts;
Disseminate information throughout the State concerning the activities and programs of the soil conservation districts and encourage the formation of districts in any areas where their organization is desirable;
Grant to the districts either directly or through the counties funds made available to the Committee for use by the districts in implementing the soil conservation program;
Provide for the execution of surety bonds for every employee or officer entrusted with funds or property;
Keep a full and accurate record of all proceedings and every rule or regulation or order issued or adopted; and
Assign to the districts such clerical and administrative employees as authorized by the annual State budget or through agreement with local governments.
